subSubSection.paragraph:
Host plants:
Monaloniines are known to feed on a wide range of plants, with some of them being pests of cocoa, tea, cashew and other cultivated plants (e.g. 
Schmitz, 1968
; de Abreu, 1977; 
Lavabre, 1977a
,b; 
Piart, 1977
; 
Hill, 1983
; 
Stonedahl, 1991
).
